<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5029283>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 5. (a) Selenops banksi, holotype male, palp, lateral, showing embolus (E), embolar sclerite (ES), and embolar base (EB) (MCZ 20436) (b) S.banksi, palp,lateral,Orellana,Ecuador (NMNH) (c) S.banksi, ex-S.kikay syn. nov., holotype male,palp,lateral,Itabuna,Brazil (note that this palp is in a slightly different orientation than preceding) (MNRJ – destroyed) (d) S.ducke, holotype male,palp,lateral,E and ES connected by weakly sclerotised area, flipped horizontally, Manaus, Brazil (MCN 25527) (e) S. ducke, holotype male, palp, lateral, E and ES connected by weakly sclerotised area, Manaus, Brazil (MCN 25527) (f) S. micropalpus, palp, lateral, E and ES are further apart than in S. banksi (A–C), King’s Hill Forest Reserve,St. Vincent and the Grenadines (CAS)." ;
